{
  "texts": [
    "Although they contained more observations than the human reports, these were not always relevant to the final diagnosis: In one case, HistoGPT mentioned a bystander cyst that was irrelevant to the diagnosis of basal cell carcinoma.",
    "In another case, the model failed to detect small objects, such as a scabies mite.",
    "On one occasion, the model incorrectly identified erythrocytes as eosinophils (Fig. 7b shows a representative example).",
    "An evaluation of the Mayo cohort showed that HistoGPT was often on the right track, but to a lesser extent than a human pathologist.",
    "In some cases, it wrote a correct microscopic description but an incorrect conclusion (either the critical findings, the final diagnosis, or both): In one case of Bowenoid squamous cell carcinoma, the microscopic description mentioned Bowenoid cells and actinic elastosis, but the critical findings concluded the presence of basal cell carcinoma."
  ]
}